  						<table align=center cellpadding='3' width='85%'>
  <tr><td class='spti2'>PLAYER JOURNAL</td></tr>  <tr><td class='db'><font class='dbti'>February 2nd.</font> - Arbaal McOwn</td></tr>
  <tr><td class='db'> </td></tr>
  <tr><td class='db'><p>Today sucked more than almost any other day in all of my EverQuest time has sucked yet... It was patch day, meaning <b>Cazic Thule</b> would be up after the patch. So we went to the PoF portal and I was really getting my hopes up of getting a <b>Cazic Skin</b> for my Epic Quest. We had around 20 people there at the PoF portal when the first people from <b>Brethren of the Mystic Dawn</b> started showing up. It seems they wanted their first shot at PoF, and they had been planning for it, altho weakly so, as we showed up hours after the patch was over. What then happened is that some bargain was struck between my guildleaders and their guildleader about that they could have Plane of Fear in return for me getting the Cazic Skin if it dropped. That hurt me, as I wanted to do it with my Guild, and not some complete band of strangers that didn´t have the slightest clue as to what the fuck they were doing. So off my guild went to Plane of Air, and I was sitting at the PoF portal with those newbies who didnt know what the fuck to do.</p>
<br>
<p>Anyway, <b>Magosian</b>, a really nice person shows up and tries to convince me to let him take my place in PoF so he can get the skin which he also needs for the Wizard epic. He was closer to it than me, but I also knew that I wouldnt have alot of chances to get the Cazic Skin... He then starts to lay down the wildest guilt trip on me and sadly, it works... Anyway, my friends modem starts fucking up and I go repeatedly linkdead over and over and over and I really felt like shit and I felt bad for Magosian too. He started offering me some actually really uber items if I let him take my place, but it wasn´t about that... I knew I had people counting on me to go in there and kill Cazic and get that skin. Hell, it wasn´t even sure that he would drop that skin, as it is still like a 1/4 drop or something. So while I feel like shit and one of the biggest criminals around, my guild is smacking up PoA badly, when suddenly something goes wrong. I kept going through a nasty LD cycle, so I had no idea what was actually going on, but I heard something about needing a repop. Anyway, the Brethren of the Mystic Dawn was getting seriously Fowned down in PoF and the guys from my guild decided to come do PoF with me then... And they did. We managed to kill ohh.. 20 mobs or so? Just enough to clear the West Wall. Then I went LD again and when I came back, the only people that were there was the peeps from Brethren of the Mystic Dawn... So I ask everyone in GC WTF is going on and all I get is silence. At this time it is around 3am my time, cause I live in Denmark, meaning it´s about 9pm EST or something... So when I finally get a response, the only one I get is "We had no clerics". WTF? Usually when we have no clerics, someone plays a damn cleric. So what´s the fucking difference this time? The only difference I can see is that they were there to help me. It´s not like I have helped pretty much ALL of them with THEIR quests, THEIR epics, THEIR ports, THEIR corpse recoveries, given THEM spells and items, helped kill the dragons that have gotten THEM their items, and pretty much without ever really asking much in return. This was the one time I really needed my guild, and they fucking let me down. Bigtime. Tons of people were sending me tells saying how wrong they could see it was and so on and bla bla bla, but no one had the fucking balls to say anything in Guildchat. No one had any fucking balls. So I spent the next 5 hours helping the Brethren who were still dying, and trying to get people to come. At 8am I collapsed in my chair and gave up and logged.</p>
<br>
<p>It turns out that a bit later in the evening, the Brethren of the Mystic Dawn had asked <b>Paragons of Fury</b> to come help them in PoF, so they did. A few hours later Cazic Thule died. Did he drop the coveted Cazic Skin that I had worked my ass off for? Yes, ofcourse he did. Grats <b>Savanna</b>... I really felt like my guild let me down bigtime that night, and I felt like shit because I had been working my fucking ass off for hours and hours and hours and days and all the goddam time so goddam much... OK, I´ll shut the hell up now, call me a dramatic prick if you want, but that´s me.</p></td></tr>
  <tr><td class='db2'><a href='view_profile.asp?Action=Journal&Id=7974'>Return to Arbaal's Journal</a></td></tr>
